
// This Hyperlambda code creates a new record in the "menu" table using the [mysql.create] slot. It specifies the table name as "menu" and provides values for the fields "dish_name", "price", and "category". The "price" field is explicitly typed as a decimal. The code ensures SQL injection protection by parameterizing the values.
mysql.create
   table:menu
   values
      dish_name:Spaghetti Carbonara
      price:decimal:12.99
      category:Pasta
